Some dogs find themselves in a shelter, like I was just a few months ago. #ad We have a shelter crisis in this country. But thankfully I was one of the luckiest dogs because I had an amazing foster family take me in, clean me up, help me come out of my shell, and find the PERFECT new human to call my own. She really got to know me through fostering, so we were sure it was a great match before we even met! I am so thankful to @marspetcareus for bringing awareness to the shelter crisis at hand, and their mission to get dogs like me fostered with their #servicehumansneeded program. Visit my link in bio to learn more about how you can answer the call through acts of service and volunteering online and in your community.

Last week was truly special! I learned about all these amazing products from my new besties, @christiebrinkley and @petlife.unlimited , and felt the power of the makeover! I first tested out things like @petlife.unlimited 's Dry Shampoo Powder and Stain & Odor Eliminator during the adoption event at @animalhaven and today I wanted to get my glam on at home with all these other goodies! First I set up their adorably designed Smart Prints Dog Pads (available at Walmart) because they're perfect for more than just pee messes and the gentle scent is so soothing for my spa time. Then I got a wipe down from nose to tail - first with the Cleansing Dog Wipes (available at Walmart) and then the Eye & Ear Dog Wipes (available at Target). Obviously, I treated myself to a pupcake as well... We were so honored to be part of this celebration of senior adoption and hope these amazing dogs find new homes soon with their makeovers. Animal Haven is very important to us - especially because our senior rescue Cupid was from there last week marked 1 year since his passing. If you live in the NYC area, there are still 10 beautiful senior dogs who would love to come home and glow up with you just like Cupid did! And if you can't adopt, please share them!! Link in @petlife.unlimited ’s bio! #ad
